_refine_special_details          
;Refined as a 2-component twin.
 Hydrogen atoms were not found in the difference map, so they were not refined
in the structure. 
 The presence of heavy atoms may explain the high values resulting from the 
Hirshfeld rigid-bond test.
 An analysis with ADDSYM in Platon does not detect that a different space group
would be better.
 The missing very strong reflections in the FCF may be blocked by the beamstop 
due to the long a-axis in this structure.
 DISP parameters were generated for this wavelength (16 KeV) using WinGX., Twin
;
